job_history.work_description: Led the organization towards eligibility in the eHealth Exchange Information Network, completed detailed survey of the county's privacy, security, confidentiality, and information exchange policies, and facilitated the processing of the Entrust Subscriber Agreement documents.

Executed the enterprise information technology strategy, partnered with the Health Services CIO and stakeholders to establish project and program governance, and supervised, led, coached, and mentored Application Support and Project Management staff.

Developed a comprehensive map and fit-gap review and analysis of the clinical workflow and electronic medical records requirements, and led a cross-functional and multi-dimensional Lean Six Sigma process improvement team.

Defined, managed, and owned the three year IT project and program roadmap, project and features prioritization, and release strategy of the web enablement of a 20/7 statewide enterprise case management, reporting, and payment system.
